binding. Chapter~\ref{chap:ip} covers the IP layer
proper.
%claude:
Chapter~\ref{chap:arp} explains ARP---how IP addresses are
resolved to Ethernet MAC addresses on a local network.
Chapter~\ref{chap:routes} covers the routing table and
how the stack decides where to send packets.
%claude:
The transport protocols are presented next:
UDP (Chapter~\ref{chap:udp}) for unreliable datagrams,
