\subsection{Network byte order}

%claude:
Network protocols use big-endian byte order, while the host
CPU may use either. The [[nhgets]]/[[hnputs]] family of
functions (defined in the \book{Libcore}) convert between
the two. [[iplong]] is a host-order 32-bit integer used when
arithmetic on IP addresses is needed---for instance, checking
whether an address falls within a route's address range.

