@
% will need that when want to do arithmetic operations on addresses,
% such as to check if they are in a certain range. See Route.

\subsection{Other address operations}

%claude:
Since IP addresses are fixed-size byte arrays (not structs),
they cannot be assigned with \verb+=+ or compared with
\verb+==+. The [[ipmove]] and [[ipcmp]] macros wrap
[[memmove]] and [[memcmp]]. [[ipcmp]] includes a fast-path
optimization: it first compares the last byte (which varies
most between addresses) before falling through to the full
16-byte comparison.

%reset, move, comparison

