%******************************************************************************
\chapter{User/Kernel Bridge}
%******************************************************************************
\label{chap:devip}

% Will see how dispatch commands from user to kernel, via /net,
% and how the kernel then dispatch internally the command to the right
% protocol, to the right method, to the right medium.

%claude:
In \plan, all network operations go through the file system.
The [[ipdevtab]] is a kernel device that serves the [[/net]]
file tree. When a user program opens [[/net/tcp/clone]], the
kernel calls [[ipopen]] which allocates a new conversation.
Writing \verb+connect 10.0.0.1!80+ to the [[ctl]] file triggers
[[ipwrite]], which dispatches to the protocol's [[connect]]
method. Reading from [[data]] dequeues packets from [[rq]].
This chapter traces how file operations are dispatched
through the [[/net]] hierarchy to the protocol implementations.

