\subsection{[[/net]] hierarchy and [[ipwalk()]]}

%claude:
[[ipgen]] generates the directory listing for each level of
the [[/net]] hierarchy. The Qid encoding packs the protocol
index, conversation index, and file type into a single 64-bit
identifier, allowing [[ipgen]] to determine from any Qid
what level of the tree it's at and what entries to show.

<<function [[ipwalk]]>>=
static Walkqid*
ipwalk(Chan* c, Chan *nc, char **name, int nname)
{
    IPaux *a = c->aux;
    Walkqid* w;

    w = devwalk(c, nc, name, nname, nil, 0, ipgen);

    if(w != nil && w->clone != nil)
        w->clone->aux = newipaux(a->owner, a->tag);

    return w;
}
@
