\subsection{Dispatch functions, [[ipxxx()]]}

%claude:
The [[ipopen]], [[ipclose]], [[ipread]], and [[ipwrite]]
functions are the kernel device methods that dispatch file
operations to the appropriate protocol or conversation.
They all follow the same pattern: extract the protocol
index and conversation number from the channel's Qid,
look up the [[Proto]] and [[Conv]], and switch on the
file type to decide what to do.

