\subsection{[[/net/x/y/data]]}

%claude:
The [[data]] file is the actual data channel. Reading
dequeues bytes from the conversation's receive queue
([[qread(cv->rq, ...)]]), and writing enqueues bytes into
the write queue ([[qwrite(cv->wq, ...)]]). The protocol's
``kick'' function (installed by [[create]]) is called
automatically when data is written, triggering the protocol
to add headers and transmit the packet.

