\subsection{TTL}

%claude:
TTL (Time To Live) limits how many gateways a packet can
traverse---each gateway decrements it by one, and the packet
is discarded when TTL reaches zero. This prevents routing
loops from circulating packets forever. The default is
[[MAXTTL]]=255.

