\section{Protocol data structures}

%claude:
[[Udppriv]] holds the protocol-wide hash table ([[Ipht]])
used to dispatch incoming packets to the right conversation
by looking up the destination port. [[Udpcb]] (the per-conversation
control block stored in [[Conv.ptcl]]) holds per-connection
state such as the ``headers'' flag for user-level UDP header
mode.

\subsection{[[Udppriv]]}

% protocol priv
<<struct [[Udppriv]]>>=
struct Udppriv
{
    // hash<(ipaddr * port) , ref<Conv>>
